sql:
SELECT characters.char_name, players.player_name, characters.level
FROM characters
INNER JOIN players ON characters.player_id = players.player_id;

external_knowledge:
- "Ventured far enough into the realm of adventure" metaphorically refers to having a high amount of experience points;
- "Exceed the mark of 750 experience points" indicates that the characters have more than 750 experience points;
- "Identities" corresponds to the names of characters;
- "Class and race affiliations" refer to the class names, class IDs, and race names;
- "Moral compasses" are the characters' alignments;
- "Tales of origin" represent the characters' background stories;
- "Wealth" refers to the gold amount;
- "Renown" is synonymous with reputation;
- "Current vitality" refers to the current hit points of characters.

Seasoned adventurers: Characters with a level greater than 5, more than 0 hit points, and more than 0 gold;
Combat stats: Include base attack bonus and types of saving throws (Fortitude, Reflex, Will);
Specialized skills: Skills that are class skills for the character.

sql:
SELECT DISTINCT p.*
FROM players p
LEFT JOIN characters c ON p.player_id = c.player_id;
